Preheat the #oven to 200 degrees.

Trim and halve the @radishes{125}. Trim the @spring onion{3} and chop widthways
into 3 pieces.

Roughly tear the @ciabatta{1} into bite sized pieces.

Pop the radishes and spring onion onto the #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@olive oil{1%tbsp}, a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast in the #oven until tender and starting to colour, ~{15-20%minutes}. Add
the torn ciabatta to the #tray halfway through roasting and give everything a
good toss. Return to the #oven for the remaining time. Keep an eye on the
bread, make sure it doesn't burn!

Meanwhile, finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(finely chopped) (stalks and
all). Zest and half the @lemon{1/2}(zested). Finely chop the
@olives{30}(finely chopped).

Drain and rinse the @butter beans{1%can} in a #sieve.

Pop half the parsley and half the lemon zest into a large #bowl. Mix in a
drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a good pinch of @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Lay a @British chicken breasts{2} on a #chopping board{} and cover with a piece
of #clingfilm. Use a #rolling pin{} or the base of a #saucepan to bash it until
it is 1cm thick all over. Repeat for the other breast(s).

Place the breasts into the #bowl with the marinade. Toss to coat the chicken
all over.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Fry the chicken until cooked and golden, ~{5-6%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle!

Meanwhile, pop the olives, the rest of the lemon zest and the parsley into a
small #bowl.

Squeeze in the juice from the lemon and season well with @pepper{}. You won't
need any salt!

Add the @olive oil{} for the tapenade (see ingredients for amount) and mix well.

Once the chicken is cooked, transfer to a #board and slice each chicken breast
into four.

Pop the roasted radishes, spring onions, croutons and butter beans into a big
#bowl. Gently mix in the @wild rocket{40}(about 1 bunch) and half the
tapenade.

Pop the salad onto plates and lay the sliced chicken on top.

Drizzle any juices left on the #tray over the chicken and spoon the remaining
tapenade all over. Now, dig in!